# Pull Request Management Rules

## PR Creation
- Write clear, descriptive PR titles
- Include a summary of changes in the PR description
- Reference related issues using `#issue-number`
- Ensure all tests pass before creating PR
- Keep PRs focused on a single concern

## PR Comments
- Be constructive and respectful
- Provide specific feedback with code suggestions
- Use inline comments for code-specific feedback
- Tag relevant reviewers with @mentions
- Respond to all review comments

## PR Merging
- Require at least one approval before merging
- Resolve all conversations before merging
- Ensure CI/CD pipeline passes
- Use squash merge for feature branches
- Delete branch after successful merge
